title: Cape Lookout National Seashore: Wildlife
body: Wildlife Photos      Â                 Shackleford Banks Horses   14 Photos  Cape Lookout National Seashore is home to a herd of more than 110 wild horses. These horses live on Shackleford Banks, the southernmost island in the park.          Sea Turtles   15 Photos  Four species of sea turtles can be found in and around Cape Lookout National Seashore--Loggerheads, Leatherbacks, Kemps Ridleys, and Greens.          Shorebirds   17 Photos  Over 200 species of birds can be found in and around Cape Lookout National Seashore at various times of the year. These are a few of the birds which have been seen in the area.            Ocean and Shoreline Creatures   14 Photos  View some of the many animals which can be found in the waters and along the beaches of Cape Lookout National Seashore.          Island Creatures   10 Photos  Discover some of the snakes, spiders, rabbits, and lizards which have adapted to life on these barrier islands.
